net.creativeparkour

Class CreativeParkourAPI

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.creativeparkour.CreativeParkourAPI

  • public class CreativeParkourAPI
extends java.lang.Object
    Main CreativeParkour API class, everything starts here!
    There are also other methods in CPUtils, but everything that directly interacts with CreativeParkour is here.
    Author:
    Obelus

      static class  CreativeParkourAPI.UnloadedPluginException
      Thrown when trying to use CreativeParkour's API if it is not loaded (CreativeParkour loads after most of other plugins, you should not try to access this API on server start).

                                             throws CreativeParkourAPI.UnloadedPluginException
        Returns a list of a player's times in all CreativeParkour maps.
        Parameters:
        playerUUID - UUID of the player we want the times.
        Returns:
        List of times of the player in all the maps

        Parameters:

      • getTimes

        public static java.util.SortedSet<CPTime> getTimes(CPMap parkourMap)
                                            throws CreativeParkourAPI.UnloadedPluginException
        Returns all the CPTimes for the given parkour map.
        Warning: this may take time if there are a lot of players!
        Parameters:
        parkourMap - CreativeParkour map we want players' times.
        Returns:
        SortedSet of all the CPTimes for the map (from the world record to the longest time).
        Throws:
        CreativeParkourAPI.UnloadedPluginException - If CreativeParkour is not loaded yet.
        Since:
        2.6
        See Also:
        CPTime

      • getParkourMaps

        public static java.util.List<CPMap> getParkourMaps()
                                            throws CreativeParkourAPI.UnloadedPluginException
        Returns all the CreativeParkour maps on the server, regardless of their CPMapState (CREATION, PUBLISHED, DOWNLOADED, DELETED), so you should check their state with map.getState().
        Returns:
        Parkour map List.
        Throws:
        CreativeParkourAPI.UnloadedPluginException - If CreativeParkour is not loaded yet.
        Since:
        2.6

      • dumpMemory

        public static void dumpMemory()
                       throws CreativeParkourAPI.UnloadedPluginException

      • getPlayerName

        public static java.lang.String getPlayerName(java.util.UUID playerUUID)
        Finds a player name with their Minecraft UUID. It asks the server for it or searches in CreativeParkour files (they may contain names from downloaded ghosts that never joined the server).
        Parameters:
        playerUUID - UUID of the player we want the name.
        Returns:
        Player's name or null if unknown.
        Since:
        2.6

      • getPlayerUUID

        public static java.util.UUID getPlayerUUID(java.lang.String playerName)
        Finds a player UUID with their name. It asks the server for it or searches in CreativeParkour files (they may contain UUIDs from downloaded ghosts that never joined the server).
        Parameters:
        playerName - Player's name (not case-sensitive).
        Returns:
        Player's UUID or null if unknown.
        Since:
        2.6

      • pluginIsLoaded

        public static boolean pluginIsLoaded()
        Checks if CreativeParkour is loaded, so if the API can be used (CreativeParkour loads after most of other plugins, you should not try to access this API on server start).
        Returns:
        true if CreativeParkour is loaded.
        Since:
        2.6
